text: The lesser moray (Gymnothorax minor) is a moray eel found in the western Pacific Ocean.Gymnothorax minor at www.fishbase.org. It was first named by Coenraad Jacob Temminck and Hermann Schlegel in 1846, and is also known as the reticulated moray eel.Common names for Gymnothorax minor at www.fishbase.org. ==References== minor Category:Fish described in 1846
